# E2E Testing Conventions

Source of truth: `docs/PlaywrightE2ETests.md`. Follow the rules below when authoring tests or any UI element exercised by tests.

> **Keep in sync:** Whenever you touch E2E work, skim `docs/PlaywrightE2ETests.md` for changes and propose updates to this rule file — but only fold in guidance that is *actionable for the agent* (conventions, patterns, do/don't). Skip prose, philosophy, or anything that doesn't change how code is written.

## data-testid (components)

- Add `data-testid` to every element a test interacts with or asserts on.
- `data-testid` MUST be the **first attribute** on the element.
- Always prefix the value with `af-`.

```tsx
// BAD
<button onClick={onFlip} className="btn">Flip</button>

// GOOD
<button data-testid="af-flip-card" onClick={onFlip} className="btn">Flip</button>
```

## Test Structure

- Use **Page Object Model**: place page classes in `tests/e2e/pages/*PageModel.ts`.
- Locators are declared as `readonly` fields, resolved via `page.getByTestId('af-...')` in the constructor.
- Wrap every public POM method with `@step('Human readable label')` to keep traces readable.
- Tests live in `tests/e2e/specs/` and consume page objects through fixtures — never `new` a page object inside a spec.
- Add JSDoc on POM classes and non-trivial methods.

## Fixtures & Imports

- Import `test` and `expect` from `@fixtures/testFixtures`, not from `@playwright/test`.
- Add new page objects to `testFixtures.ts` so specs receive them via destructuring.
- Use TypeScript path aliases (`@pages/*`, `@fixtures/*`, `@support/*`) — no relative paths like `../../pages/...`.

```ts
// GOOD
import { test, expect } from '@fixtures/testFixtures'

test('flips card', async ({ studyPage }) => {
  await studyPage.startSession()
  await studyPage.flipCard()
})
```

## Assertions & Hygiene

- Prefer Playwright web-first assertions (`toBeVisible`, `toHaveText`) — never `expect(await locator.textContent())`.
- Use `expect.soft(...)` for non-blocking assertions where it improves diagnostics.
- Keep tests **small, focused, happy-path** unless the feature is shipped and stable.
- After a new dev phase: run all tests → fix regressions → add tests for new features.

## Quality & Tooling

- Follow existing project standards for all test-related files (`tests/e2e/**`, Playwright config, test fixtures, and test documentation updates).
- Format test changes with project formatter (`npm run format`) when needed for consistency.
- Ensure lint passes before finalizing E2E changes (`npm run lint`).
- Ensure unit tests still pass when shared logic/config is touched (`npm run test`).
- Ensure Playwright suite passes after E2E changes (`npm run test:e2e`).
- Avoid introducing test-only lint bypasses; if unavoidable, scope them narrowly and document why.
- Keep naming and casing consistent with current repository patterns (fixtures, page models, spec names, and TC IDs).

## Test List

- When adding any new tests, add it to `docs/TestCases.md` to maintain list of current tests coverage. Just high level description, not too detailed.
- Use a Markdown table format with columns: `Test Case ID`, `Title`, `Coverage`.
- Use sequential IDs in the format `TC001`, `TC002`, `TC003`, ...
- Add one row per test scenario with concise high-level wording.
- Prefix each Playwright test title with the matching test case ID (example: `test('TC001 | App shell and theme toggle render', ...)`).
- Keep Playwright test title IDs and title text in sync with `docs/TestCases.md`.